Wądzyn  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dąbrówno, within Ostróda County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south of Dąbrówno,  south of Ostróda, and  south-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
